  "prompt": "Can I reapply a US tourist visa 3 months after the previous refusal?",
  "response": "There's no strict waiting period to reapply for a US tourist visa after a refusal. However, you should:\n\n1. Address the reasons for the previous refusal\n- Provide additional supporting documents\n- Demonstrate stronger ties to your home country\n- Clarify any misunderstandings from the previous application\n\n2. Wait until you have new or stronger evidence\n- Gather more compelling proof of:\n  - Financial stability\n  - Intent to return home\n  - Purpose of travel\n\n3. Prepare a stronger application\n- Complete the DS-160 form carefully\n- Have all required documents ready\n- Be honest and consistent in your interview\n\n4. Consider seeking advice from an immigration attorney if the previous refusal was complex\n\nRemember, each application is evaluated individually, and there's no guarantee of approval. The key is to demonstrate strong reasons for your temporary visit and intent to return to your home country.",
